		<div>Except that no stun of ours of any kind will ever land, and using any non lure spell in a duel is just a waste of time.  The only way we can interrupt casts is with CoX (that works really well vs. casters).  Also flux staff only affects FR and CR.  So really its all about resists.  If you manage to root the pet, use epic and frenzy and chain cast your best lure.  Or depending on how weak the mage is you can just tank the pet.  <br />
<br />
Normally even with malo you should resist most of what mages cast on you and with all of our spell shelding their nukes are quite laughable, but a bst is far more tricky since you need to be shadow steping all the time and of course they heal (though crappy it is).  <br />
<br />
Finally using MB in a duel is always a very bad idea nowdays.  I've had other wizards MB me when I was at 40% and I would lose only about 3k hp, for some reason the way it is mittigated in pvp make it really inefective.</div>
	</td>
